<plot>An independent production picked up for distribution by the shorts department of Warner Brothers. Directed and photographed by the Florida-based Ted and Vincent Saizis, who confined most of their work (features and shorts) to the southeastern United States (and most of that done in the Okeefenokee park and swamp areas of Georgia and Florida), and some second-unit work for many major companies in other areas of the U.S. This one involves the tracking down and killing of a rogue bear, in Georgia's Okeefenokee Swamp Park, by a party of swamp men led by naturalist David Da Lie.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?072992</url></doc>
